Design an in-memory message queue (similar to a scaled-down Kafka or RabbitMQ) that supports a publisher-subscriber model, but with the added complexity of Consumer Groups and Fault Tolerance.

Functional Requirements
Topic Management: Users should be able to create topics.
Publish: Producers can publish messages to a specific topic.
Subscribe: Consumers can subscribe to a topic.
Consumer Groups (The core challenge):
Consumers can belong to a "Consumer Group."
Broadcast Mode: If consumers are in different groups, a message published to the topic is broadcast to all groups (every group gets a copy).
Point-to-Point Mode: If multiple consumers are in the same group, a message published to the topic is delivered to only one available consumer in that group.
Retry & DLQ: If a consumer throws an exception while processing a message, the broker should retry delivering it a configurable number of times. If it exhausts the retries, the message should be moved to a Dead Letter Queue (DLQ).

